  "title": "Senior Data Analyst, Gaming (12-months contract)",
  "description": "<p><strong>This is a 12-months contract role.</strong></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Partner with Strategic Partner Managers and key stakeholders to develop regional strategies grounded in data insights.</li><li>Proactively identify business opportunities and deliver actionable recommendations through deep-dive analyses.</li><li>Manage and consult with strategic gaming developers to support their growth and success on the platform.</li><li>Track, analyze, and communicate key performance metrics to support product and partnership goals.</li><li>Build, maintain, and optimize performance tracking dashboards using SQL and business intelligence tools.</li><li>Act as a subject matter expert in data analysis and data mining, providing trend analysis and insights to leadership and partners.</li><li>Support business development efforts through insights generation, strategic planning, and participation in partner meetings.</li><li>Support day-to-day data operations and reporting with both internal and external teams.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><strong>8+ years of experience in data analysis, business intelligence, or a related technical or analytics role. Prior experience working in or closely with the gaming industry will be a plus.</strong></li><li>Bachelor’s degree in a quantitative field such as Economics, Statistics, Business, Computer Science, or equivalent practical experience.</li><li>Advanced proficiency in SQL and experience with analytical tools such as Python and BI platforms (e.g., Tableau, Power BI, or similar).</li><li>Demonstrated ability to independently identify problems, design analyses, and deliver actionable insights in ambiguous environments.</li><li>Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to translate complex data into clear, compelling narratives.</li><li>Advanced skills in Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint.</li></ul>",
